# Writing

- **Technical voice (default)** — concise, direct, list-friendly, non-patronizing (consistent
  with root `AGENTS.md` Communication guardrail). Applies to design write-ups, implementation
  explanations, README usage sections, and API/behavior docs.
- **Narrative/conceptual voice (exception, not default)** — reserved for explicitly
  reflective/retrospective/historical writing (project retrospectives, origin stories). Still
  concise — reflective tone, not verbose tone.
- **No process narrative in state-describing docs** — keep task, ticket, PR, review-discussion,
  or session-specific narrative out of state-describing documentation (README, design/API docs);
  describe the system as it is now, citing durable references where useful. That process history
  belongs in the appropriate record (see `my-audit-trail`), or in a project retrospective if
  genuinely worth preserving long-term.
- **Out of scope** — code comments/docstrings (see `my-commenting`); commit messages, PR
  descriptions, Jira comments, incident notes (see `my-audit-trail`); terse operational/status
  responses (no styling needed).
